HEADWORD: Candidating
<hw>Can"di*da`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The taking of
the position of a candidate; specifically, the preaching of a clergyman
with a view to settlement.</def> <mark>[Cant, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

